Cool! Continuing the intro to the fandom; Adam worked with two other brothers to produce music up until 2007 when he branched out to focus on his solo project Owl City, with the help of the aforementioned brothers. He recorded his own albums in the basement AC room of his parents house, filmed his own music videos, and distributed his own CDs. Combined with intense online marketing through MySpace, eventually his songs reached the top 100 despite not having a label. He was quickly picked up by a massive record company known as Universal Music Group, todays republic records.
